about a person by just looking at them.

13:10.332 --> 13:11.249
Okay.

13:14.336 --> 13:15.712
So, what'd you figure out about me?

13:17.047 --> 13:17.881
Not a thing.

13:25.889 --> 13:26.932
How do I know you?

13:28.725 --> 13:30.769
I know you from something.

13:32.187 --> 13:33.396
If you say so.

13:34.689 --> 13:35.982
Are you an actor?

13:37.901 --> 13:38.985
Yeah.

13:41.071 --> 13:43.198
All the actors I know are
self-centered and insane.

13:45.826 --> 13:47.327
Sounds about right.

13:54.209 --> 13:55.627
You're staring at me now?

13:56.878 --> 13:57.921
Yeah.

13:59.089 --> 14:02.425
Seeing if I can... figure you out.

14:03.927 --> 14:04.761
Can you?

14:06.972 --> 14:08.098
You seem sad.

14:11.351 --> 14:12.352
There you go.

14:13.270 --> 14:14.312
Thanks.

14:15.355 --> 14:17.274
It's all here, but... count it.

14:18.817 --> 14:20.068
Don't drink too much with these.

14:20.986 --> 14:22.070
Thanks.

14:25.782 --> 14:27.951
Jesus! Get some sun, man.

14:29.119 --> 14:30.412
Nice to meet you, um...

14:32.497 --> 14:33.915
Sorry, I forgot your name.

14:34.124 --> 14:36.710
- Lee.
- Right. Lee.

14:38.128 --> 14:40.297
They say that memory
is the second thing to go.

14:42.215 --> 14:43.717
And what's the first?

14:44.134 --> 14:45.218
I can't remember.

14:48.305 --> 14:49.389
How do you two know each other?

14:51.224 --> 14:52.767
We were on a TV show together.

14:53.351 --> 14:54.561
Nothing you've ever heard of.

14:55.186 --> 14:57.814
<i>It's called Cattle Drive.
It ran for 13 episodes.</i>

14:58.565 --> 14:59.524
Lee was the lead.

15:00.108 --> 15:01.613
Ben Horn, a gun slinger.

15:01.693 --> 15:02.527
Whoa.

15:02.736 --> 15:05.655
I was a cocky kid who stole
the wrong man's horse.

15:06.406 --> 15:08.116
- You mean you had a real job once?
- Yeah.

15:08.742 --> 15:10.744
Had a wife too. So did he.

15:11.703 --> 15:12.954
Now, we just have each other.

15:14.289 --> 15:15.415
Well.

15:17.250 --> 15:19.127
Nice to meet you, Lee.

15:57.749 --> 15:59.250
This one, and this one.

16:07.634 --> 16:08.718
What a nice surprise.

16:09.928 --> 16:11.137
A nice surprise?

16:17.811 --> 16:18.728
Good to see you, Val.

16:19.104 --> 16:19.938
Sure it is.

16:31.825 --> 16:33.243
You getting ready for another show?

16:34.160 --> 16:35.578
Yes, at the end of the month.

16:49.884 --> 16:51.386
Have you seen Lucy recently?

16:52.721 --> 16:56.016
Yes, she came over for dinner,
we watched some TV on Sunday.

17:01.396 --> 17:02.313
What'd you watch?

17:04.107 --> 17:06.108
You wanna know what
we watched on television?

17:07.068 --> 17:08.569
I haven't seen Lucy in a long time.

17:08.862 --> 17:09.695
Call her.

17:10.405 --> 17:11.740
She doesn't want me to call her.

17:12.115 --> 17:12.949
Don't do that.

17:14.534 --> 17:15.452
I don't blame her.

17:22.791 --> 17:23.960
You should call her.

17:45.815 --> 17:47.400
I've got something I wanna tell you.

17:56.576 --> 17:57.577
I'm gonna make a movie.

18:05.168 --> 18:06.086
<i>Peter Cohen's office.</i>

18:06.461 --> 18:08.383
Hey, Chelsea, it's Lee, for Peter.

18:08.463 --> 18:11.299
<i>- Hi, Lee, let me see if I have him.
- Thanks.</i>

18:14.928 --> 18:16.179
<i>Lee, what's up?</i>

18:16.513 --> 18:18.681
When did you say that thing was again?

18:19.182 --> 18:21.351
<i>- The Western award?
- Yeah.</i>

18:47.710 --> 18:48.753
Dad.

18:49.462 --> 18:50.630
You look good out there.

18:53.925 --> 18:55.260
Remember when we used to play?

18:58.346 --> 18:59.389
What are you doing here?

19:02.392 --> 19:03.810
I mean, how did you know I was here?

19:04.769 --> 19:05.687
Your mother told me.

19:07.313 --> 19:09.065
I was in the neighborhood, and I just...

19:12.902 --> 19:13.862
How's work going?

19:14.988 --> 19:16.739
Still waiting tables at that steakhouse?

19:17.740 --> 19:18.700
I liked that place.

19:21.828 --> 19:22.954
I work for Google.

19:24.497 --> 19:25.373
Oh.

19:26.249 --> 19:27.792
Yeah, I sell advertising space for them.

19:29.169 --> 19:30.003
Wow.

19:32.046 --> 19:33.214
Yeah.

19:34.716 --> 19:35.592
What's up?

19:37.594 --> 19:38.761
Oh.

19:39.804 --> 19:41.518
I guess it's been a while, huh?

19:41.598 --> 19:42.724
Yeah.

19:44.934 --> 19:45.935
You look the same though.

19:47.020 --> 19:48.396
That's good, I guess.

19:54.569 --> 19:55.778
I was thinking, uh...

19:59.449 --> 20:02.702
I'm getting this lifetime
achievement award thing, and uh...

20:03.620 --> 20:05.455
it's no big deal but,

20:08.374 --> 20:12.086
I was thinking maybe you'd like
to go with me to the ceremony.

20:16.007 --> 20:17.008
When is it?

20:17.675 --> 20:18.593
Sunday.

20:19.844 --> 20:20.678
This Sunday?

20:21.930 --> 20:24.140
I'm going to Palm Springs
with Jake. I can't cancel.

20:25.391 --> 20:26.434
Right.

20:28.061 --> 20:29.020
Okay.

20:30.897 --> 20:32.315
How about dinner when you get back?

20:34.192 --> 20:37.737
My treat. You pick the place,
time, whatever.

20:44.244 --> 20:45.203
I'm free Tuesday.

20:47.163 --> 20:48.998
Yeah. Yeah, that'll be great.

20:52.794 --> 20:53.711
I got to get back.

21:02.262 --> 21:04.389
I'll see ya. Tuesday.

21:13.773 --> 21:17.068
<i>♪ I'm gonna have some fun ♪</i>

21:18.528 --> 21:23.157
<i>♪ On the beach where there's a party ♪</i>

21:28.579 --> 21:33.293
<i>♪ On the beach Where there's a party... ♪</i>

21:35.753 --> 21:36.838
Hello?

21:37.130 --> 21:40.300
<i>Hello, Mr. Hayden?
It's Nina calling from Cedars-Sinai.</i>

21:41.050 --> 21:44.512
<i>Dr. Friedburg would like to schedule
your first oncology appointment.</i>

21:45.888 --> 21:47.056
Oh?

21:47.432 --> 21:49.809
<i>Are you available
tomorrow morning at 11:00?</i>

21:51.477 --> 21:52.812
Tomorrow morning?

21:54.439 --> 21:55.315
Um...

21:55.690 --> 21:57.859
<i>Dr. Friedburg would
like to discuss your treatment plan</i>

21:58.026 --> 21:59.610
<i>with you as soon as possible.</i>

22:01.863 --> 22:04.198
<i>Is there another time
that might be better for you?</i>

22:06.117 --> 22:08.536
I'm actually in the middle
of something right now, could...

22:09.120 --> 22:11.497
<i>- Can I call you back?
- Yeah, that's fine.</i>

24:29.677 --> 24:31.262
Best tacos in L.A., right?

24:31.888 --> 24:32.972
Yeah.

24:33.973 --> 24:35.099
You live around here?

24:35.516 --> 24:36.476
No.

24:37.894 --> 24:39.645
Stalking you.

24:40.313 --> 24:41.397
Yeah.

24:44.358 --> 24:45.276
Charlotte, right?

24:46.903 --> 24:48.446
Got a good memory for an old pot-head.

24:49.405 --> 24:50.823
A sad old pot-head.

24:52.116 --> 24:53.576
Why did you say that anyway?

24:54.911 --> 24:58.247
Um, because you're old
and you smoke a lot of weed.

24:59.207 --> 25:00.833
I mean, the part about me being sad.

25:04.128 --> 25:05.129
I don't know.

25:06.214 --> 25:07.340
Are you?

25:10.927 --> 25:12.178
Nothing wrong with that.

25:20.978 --> 25:21.896
Are you married?

25:23.606 --> 25:26.234
Divorced. Have been for a long time.

25:31.280 --> 25:32.532
So are you gonna ask for my number?

25:35.535 --> 25:36.577
You want me to?

25:39.747 --> 25:40.790
Yeah.

25:42.041 --> 25:44.585
What? You got a thing for
sad old guys or something?

25:45.294 --> 25:47.046
No.

25:47.213 --> 25:48.339
Just old guys.

25:58.975 --> 26:00.226
You doing anything on Sunday night?

26:21.414 --> 26:22.582
Cheers.

26:23.624 --> 26:25.126
To achieving things in a lifetime.

26:25.543 --> 26:26.711
Sure.

26:28.754 --> 26:32.842
<i>♪ You keep on moving in and out, girl ♪</i>

26:33.134 --> 26:35.261
<i>♪ You keep on moving ♪</i>

26:39.432 --> 26:40.808
What's that?

26:42.435 --> 26:43.811
Fairy powder.

26:44.312 --> 26:45.563
Uh-huh.

26:47.231 --> 26:49.483
It's something that
will make you feel great.

26:51.402 --> 26:52.945
I'm feeling pretty good right now.

26:54.697 --> 26:55.906
Oh, yeah?

26:58.034 --> 27:01.037
<i>♪ You keep on moving... ♪</i>

27:05.041 --> 27:08.794
It won't kill you, I promise.
But no peer pressure.

27:11.797 --> 27:12.882
Give me that stuff.

27:20.348 --> 27:23.309
You really like burning the candle
at both ends, don't you?

27:24.185 --> 27:25.728
It seems like you do too.

27:34.695 --> 27:35.696
You know who came up with that?

27:37.323 --> 27:38.574
"Burning the candle at both ends"?

27:39.950 --> 27:40.785
Who's that?

27:42.078 --> 27:43.663
Edna St. Vincent Millay.

27:49.710 --> 27:53.756
"My candle burns at both ends,
it will not last the night,

27:55.007 --> 27:57.510
"But, ah, my foes, and oh, my friends,

27:57.718 --> 27:59.679
It gives a lovely light!"

28:02.223 --> 28:03.307
Isn't it great?

28:04.558 --> 28:05.851
<i>It's called First Fig.</i>

28:14.276 --> 28:15.319
What?

28:18.072 --> 28:19.281
I'm thinking.

28:20.700 --> 28:21.992
What are you thinking?

28:23.494 --> 28:26.372
That if you were maybe
20 years older, I'd probably kiss you.

28:27.832 --> 28:29.125
I got to wait 20 years?

28:29.834 --> 28:31.085
You'll be dead in 20 years.

28:33.170 --> 28:34.547
Don't remind me.

28:40.052 --> 28:41.345
So, you're ready for tonight?

28:44.473 --> 28:45.558
Not really.

28:48.018 --> 28:49.186
Are you gonna give a speech?

28:52.148 --> 28:53.524
They'll be expecting that.

28:54.275 --> 28:56.277
Just talk about all your
lifetime achievements.

28:59.113 --> 29:00.906
I did one film that I'm proud of.

29:02.158 --> 29:03.534
That was 40 years ago.

29:04.452 --> 29:07.121
Since then, I've stayed busy,
but I wouldn't say I've been...

29:09.373 --> 29:10.291
achieving.

29:12.960 --> 29:16.839
It's kinda weird being remembered
for one part for so many years.

29:17.882 --> 29:18.924
Yeah?

29:21.385 --> 29:24.180
But it's about as close to immortality
as any person can get.

29:25.639 --> 29:26.807
You haven't even seen it.

29:27.433 --> 29:28.726
I don't need to see it.

29:30.186 --> 29:31.479
I've got you right here.

29:33.355 --> 29:34.607
Got the man himself.

29:37.026 --> 29:38.277
The Hero.

29:42.448 --> 29:43.532
Okay.

29:54.835 --> 29:58.172
<i>♪ If you love somebody enough ♪</i>

29:59.507 --> 30:02.551
<i>♪ You'll follow wherever they go ♪</i>

30:03.135 --> 30:05.429
So, when is this
fairy powder going to kick in?

30:06.013 --> 30:06.931
Pretty soon.

30:07.389 --> 30:10.392
And then this is going to seem like
the greatest party of all time.

30:11.060 --> 30:12.061
It better.

30:12.603 --> 30:13.729
Mr. Hayden.

30:13.979 --> 30:16.106
- Please, call me Lee.
- Gary.

30:16.524 --> 30:19.318
Gary Babcock, I'm the...
the president of the...

30:19.860 --> 30:21.862
the Western Appreciation
and Preservation Guild.

30:22.279 --> 30:23.656
We're... we're so honored
to have you here.

30:23.989 --> 30:25.157
I'm honored to be here, Gary.

30:25.699 --> 30:27.409
- This is...
- Hi, I'm Cathy Lee.

30:27.660 --> 30:28.494
Cathy Lee.

30:31.956 --> 30:33.374
- Funny.
- Isn't it?

30:33.541 --> 30:36.836
When I met him I thought,
this must be meant to be.

30:38.128 --> 30:38.963
Uh-huh.

30:39.839 --> 30:43.425
This is such a cool event,
such a... diverse crowd.

30:43.968 --> 30:46.804
Uh, yeah. Sure.

30:48.138 --> 30:52.104
Well, would you mind stepping over?
We'd like to get a few pictures.

30:52.184 --> 30:53.060
